# WebRTC signaling add-on (standalone)

## Repo scope

All signaling server work lives in **`webrtc_signaling/`** (`package.json` name: `webrtc-signaling-addon`).
GitHub: **[Shaffer-Softworks/WebRTC-signaling-server](https://github.com/Shaffer-Softworks/WebRTC-signaling-server)**.

The **RPI** Android repo is a *consumer*; it keeps a Node-RED export only as legacy reference.
Deep context: **`webrtc_signaling/SIGNALING_CONTEXT.md`**.

## Architecture

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `server.js` | HTTP + WS server, session map, dual ping (WS-level + app-level), OpenObserve log hook |
| `signaling.js` | Protocol router (`register`, `offer/answer/candidate`, `hangup`, `heartbeat`, `pong`), stale prune, `terminateSession` on eviction |
| `verify-terminate-parity.test.js` | 4 tests: eviction, stale prune, pong handling, unregistered pong error |

## Dual ping keepalive (proxy-safe)

- Supervisor supplies **`/data/options.json`**: `port`, `openobserve_url`, `openobserve_username`, `openobserve_password` (Basic auth when both user and password set). Image base **Node 20 Alpine** (`build.yaml` / `Dockerfile`).
- User-facing URLs: dashboard **`/`**, WebSocket **`/webrtc`**, JSON **`/api/clients`** (`meta` may include process + host CPU/RAM samples for the dashboard — see **`SIGNALING_CONTEXT.md`** → *Dashboard and GET /api/clients*).
- **Supervisor packaging** (schema, `build.yaml` image paths, store URL `#main`, icon): see **`webrtc_signaling/SIGNALING_CONTEXT.md`** → *Home Assistant add-on (Supervisor) — saved context*.
Reverse proxies (HAProxy / OPNsense, nginx) often ignore **WebSocket control-frame** pings (opcode 0x9) for idle timeout purposes.
Only **data frames** (text/binary, opcode 0x1/0x2) reliably reset their tunnel idle timer.

| Mechanism | Interval | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| **WS-level ping** (`ws.ping()`) | 30s (`WS_PING_INTERVAL_MS`) | Detects dead TCP sockets; `ws.terminate()` if no pong |
| **App-level ping** (`{"type":"ping","ts":…}`) | 25s (`APP_PING_INTERVAL_MS`) | JSON data frame that keeps proxy tunnel alive |
| **Client heartbeat** (`{"type":"heartbeat"}`) | ~30s (sent by Android app) | Upstream data frame; resets `lastActivity` for stale prune |

If `ws_ping_timeout` or `server closed connection` appears in logs, check the **proxy** `timeout tunnel` / `proxy_read_timeout`. The app-level ping at 25s should survive any proxy with timeout >= 30s.

## Stale client prune

`STALE_CLIENT_MS = 90000` (90s). Clients with no `lastActivity` update are pruned on the next `buildClientsList()` call. Pruned sessions get `terminateSession(sid)` (force-closes the WS). The Android app sends heartbeat every ~30s, well inside the 90s window.

## `not_registered` flow

If a message arrives for a `sessionId` not in `sessInfo`, the server replies `{"type":"error","message":"not_registered"}`. Common causes:
- Session was **evicted** (same `clientId` re-registered from a new socket)
- Session was **pruned** as stale
- Session was **terminated** by WS ping timeout

The Android app responds with `forceSignalingReconnect()` → new socket + `register`.

## OpenObserve logging

`onLog(payload, level)` → stdout + optional HTTP POST to OpenObserve ingest URL (configured via `/data/options.json` or env vars).
Events logged: `registered`, `disconnect`, `websocket_close`, `websocket_error`, `ws_ping_timeout`, `clientsList`, `heartbeat` (debug), `not_registered` (warn).

Stream: typically `node_red` (because the ingest URL path includes the stream name); `service: "webrtc-signaling"`, `tag: "webrtc"`.

## HA add-on packaging

| Topic | Key detail |
|-------|-----------|
| **Layout** | Root `repository.yaml`; add-on folder `webrtc_signaling/` matches `slug: webrtc_signaling` in `config.yaml` |
| **`build.yaml`** | `build_from` must be full image refs (e.g. `docker.io/library/node:20-alpine`); short names rejected by Supervisor |
| **Dockerfile** | `ARG BUILD_FROM` / `FROM $BUILD_FROM`; `npm install --omit=dev` (no lockfile → `npm ci` fails) |
| **Options** | `/data/options.json`: `port`, `openobserve_url`, `openobserve_username`, `openobserve_password` |
| **Port** | Schema: `int(1,65535)?`; default 8765 |

## Testing

```bash
npm test                          # if node is available locally
# or via Docker (matches add-on base image):
DOCKER_HOST=unix:///var/run/docker.sock \
  docker run --rm -v "$(pwd):/app:ro" -w /app node:22-alpine node verify-terminate-parity.test.js
```

